	   <tr><td colspan=2>Before level 30, mana gear is generally more helpful than plain wisdom gear. (i.e. I'd rather have a 5 mana ring than a 2 wis ring on my new druid). Better also to invest in a few good pieces (such as velium jasper rings) than 2 wis ring here, 2 wis ring there which will just have to be upgraded in a few more levels.<br><br>What importance you place upon AC is another personal choice: if your druid is never going to dirty his/her fingers in melee, you can afford to bypass AC for more stats. Would you rather have a 0AC 3STR 3WIS platinum armband or get the 8AC 3WIS (-3DEX) of Ulthork Hide Arms? My druid appreciates the AC so I've made those choices: Charred Guardian Shield instead of Testament of Vanear, for instance.<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Ancarett, who lives at <a href="http://ancarett.com" target=_new>http://ancarett.com</a></td></tr>
