	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.35]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fear kiting: As a Druid you can only fear mobs that are defined as an animal, you already knew that ...moving on, snare the animal first so it doesn't get to far away, now you can either stick it good with a few DoT's(you'll get your first one at 14) then fear it, or fear it first then DoT it. Sit down and med til it's time to refresh snare or DoT's, repeat until it falls down dead.<br><br>Root/Rot: Root the mob, any mob, now DoT the poor thing and med til Root needs a refresh(it's a good idea to snare it so it doesn't have the chance to reach you while you try to reroot it). Rinse and repeat.<br><br>That's it, that simple, this way you can solo with full health and lots of mana at the end of every fight with little risk of death.<br><br>Seedplant<br>15 druid<br>torvonnilous<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Jan 26 00:31:35 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
