	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmm, if you go the quick exp route, 450-600 hours should put you between L40 and L50 somewhere.<br>You do not write how you spend your time and why it takes so longs, so i can only give some general tips:<br>- Do not die. If you can take out that red MOB<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;with little risk, fine. But if you die every<br>  second try, you get nowhere.<br>- Get a group. While soloing a druid at higher<br>  levels can give insane exp, a L12 druid is not<br>  really good at it. Also there will be people<br>  there who can tell you if you make any mistakes.<br>- Use all your resources when you solo. Buy all<br>  your spells (ecept maybe the real senseless<br>  like Starlight) and learn what every single one<br>  does. If you solo, melee a bit. When you<br>  meditate (you have trained one point in<br>  meditation and look at your spellbook between<br>  fights, right?), it makes no sense to be at full<br>  HP. Balance damage taken and mana spent so that<br>  both will be full at the same time without<br>  healing yourself.<br>- Ask other players ingame if you have questions<br>  there is a lot of helpful people around that<br>  can help you.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Nindor<br>L65 Dwarven Cleric on Zebuxoruk<br>Stone</td></tr>
