	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, now THIS I agree with you on, kind of. :) In ANY case, when you are in a group, do what the group needs you to do, not what you want to or what you think is cool. That gets groups killed. For a druid, that can be a lot of things (nuke, debuff, traffic control, and EVEN melee), but that is not up to you to decide. If the group has a cleric, why waste mana healing? If the group has melee fighters, why wade into battle. HOWEVER, if the tanks are low on hp and there isn't a good backup, go ahead and tank. If the cleric is low on mana, get up and heal a bit. If your chanter is oom, work on traffic control. A good druid works on all of these skills (on their OWN time, not the group's), so that they can take over those roles (however inferior to the classes that specialize in them) if need be, or fill those roles as needed by the group. My 2cp.<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>[Druid] Lambeau Farstrider (Human)<br>[Rogue] Gripp Tinkersnout (Gnome)<br>&lt;Tragic Heroes&gt; -- Saryrn</td></tr>
