	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101108074768180><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101108074768180>RE: what to do now</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101108074768180#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=94596><span id= >tuoneves</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 15th 2:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got finished leveling from 44 to 48 by kiting the dwarfs in Butcher Block. The EXP is very good and the loot is pretty good...made 200 to 250pp a night.<br>If you know the right dwarfs to kite you only take a faction hit with the citizens of kaladim.<br>(the guards wont bother you)<br>Here was the most efficient way i found to do it.<br>go to the Docks where you load the boat to FV, the large area inside the walls is your work area.<br>There are 4 dwarfs there that are good to kite...<br>2 are in the 3rd and 4th huts on the left as you enter the docks area and the other 2 are at the end of the 2 docks.<br>Their first names are GLORIN, DORIN, GANN, and MAGNUS.<br>These guys are on a fairly long spawn so here is how you can stay busy (and efficient with your time)<br>Just outside the docks...straight ahead are the Tombstones....there are 2 female dwarfs there also.(dont remeber their names) so if you include them, that makes a total of 6 dwarfs in that area to kite.<br>Here is what you do.....<br>Pull and snare the 2 dwarfs in the huts and the one on the end of the right dock, kite them in the dock area....when done sit and med....when full mana go and run out to the tombstones and pull the 2 from there back to the docks area (dont snare them at the stones it will take to long for them to get to the docks...just let them chase you into the dock area and then snare them) Next go to the dwarf on the far left dock (magnus)and add them to your 2 from the tombstones...kite away, when done just med up and the first 3 will be ready to go again...<br>Thats it...(oh yeah, you can sell to the merchant right at the docks also so you never need to leave)<br>I was able to blow thru levels 45 46 and 47 using this method in a very short time, at 48 the dwarfs turned light blue and I moved on to timorous Deep.<br>Good luck<br>Tuoneves &lt;Lords of the Crimson Cubes&gt;<br>49th Druid<br>lany's<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
